article.description: Tim Abruzzo and Shawn Anderson scored 11 points apiece and Navy hung on to beat Penn 65-59 Wednesday night for its seventh straight victory.
article.headline: Navy holds on to top Penn 65-59 for 7th straight win
article.linkText: Navy holds on to top Penn 65-59 for 7th straight win
article.story: PHILADELPHIA -- Tim Abruzzo and Shawn Anderson scored 11 points apiece and Navy hung on to beat Penn 65-59 Wednesday night for its seventh straight victory. It's the longest winning streak for Navy (7-2) since 2009. Penn used a 7-0 run to cut Navy's lead to 57-55 with 2:11 left. Darien Nelson-Henry's free throw with 1:03 remaining pulled the Quakers within one, the closest they came in the second half. Anderson answered with a layup and hit two free throws with 16 seconds left for a four-point lead. Abruzzo and Anderson both went 4 of 8 from the field and Abruzzo made all three of the team's 3-pointers. Despite shooting 50 percent from the field -- 57 percent in the second half -- Penn couldn't overcome a 12-point halftime lead. Antonio Woods had 16 points on 7-of-13 shooting for Penn (4-3), which turned it over 18 times resulting in 22 Navy points.
